From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: zcop <zcop@local>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 22:15:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: qcom: ipq5018: rename qpic nand node for u-boot fixup

Some Xiaomi IPQ5018 bootloaders try to patch NAND DT properties through a
hardcoded node path:

  /soc/qpic-nand@79b0000

Mainline DTS names this node as "spi@79b0000", which causes those fixups to
miss and may break boot argument / NAND related handoff behavior on these
boards.

Keep the same register address and functionality, but rename the node to match
the bootloader expectation.

Signed-off-by: zcop <zcop@local>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq5018.dtsi | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq5018.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq5018.dtsi
@@ -559,7 +559,7 @@
 			status = "disabled";
 		};
 
-		qpic_nand: spi@79b0000 {
+		qpic_nand: qpic-nand@79b0000 {
 			compatible = "qcom,ipq5018-snand", "qcom,ipq9574-snand";
